sub_topic: Prove that the Cartesian product of two sets is not commutative.
message_1: Let A = {1, 2, 3} and B = {4, 5}. Find out the Cartesian product of A and B which is A x B. Also, compute the Cartesian product of B and A which is B x A. Show that A x B is not equal to B x A to prove that the Cartesian product of two sets is not commutative.
